name: Enso
headline: Self-Service Data Prep and Blend Built for Data Teams.
description:
Enso Analytics is a self-service data prep and analysis platform for data teams. It transforms complex processes into repeatable workflows, saving users 7 hours weekly. With full configuration visibility, seamless environment transitions, and real-time updates, Enso caters to both non-programmers and developers, offering cloud and desktop options.

DEMO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OBrYjpgCSEE

# Catalog for workflows and data, no matter where they reside.
**Everyone has access to the right data and workflows.** Tag, document, search, and discover data based on its format, usage, structure, and location.
# Data Links.
**Shortcuts to files, databases, queries and APIs. Update data sources without editing your workflows.** Save time and reduce the risk of using last month's data. Update the data link with current file or connection string information and all workflows that reference the data link now point to the current data.
# Version history for all!
**Workflows, data files and data links. Versioned and auto-saved every time.** Never lose your work. Make updates without worry because you can always restore an older version.

# Unified data security and classification.
**Data Links sharing operates at a granular level, from complete datasets to single query results** , and can be based on classification, such as importance or risk level. 
**Data Links can store encrypted credentials** to shield against social engineering and usage ofrecycled or default passwords, the most common causes of data breaches.
# Comprehensive access and usage logging.
**User activity is logged and searchable, empowering governance.**

**Address missing values, correct errors, and reshape data** by transforming, combining, aggregating and filtering.
# Blend and process data in‚Äëdatabase and in‚Äëmemory.

# Integrated workflow documentation
**Enables you to recall what you have done, and others in the organization to interpret what you have built.** Since it is integrated as part of the workflow, version history is built in!

# Catalog for workflows and data, no matter where they reside.
**Everyone has access to the right data and workflows.** Tag, document, search, and discover data based on its format, usage, structure, and location.
# Data Links.
**Shortcuts to files, databases, queries and APIs. Update data sources without editing your workflows.** Save time and reduce the risk of using last month's data. Update the data link with current file or connection string information and all workflows that reference the data link now point to the current data.
# Version history for all!
**Workflows, data files and data links. Versioned and auto-saved every time.** Never lose your work. Make updates without worry because you can always restore an older version.
coming soon
# Unified data security and classification.
**Data Links sharing operates at a granular level, from complete datasets to single query results** , and can be based on classification, such as importance or risk level. 
**Data Links can store encrypted credentials** to shield against social engineering and usage ofrecycled or default passwords, the most common causes of data breaches.
# Comprehensive access and usage logging.
**User activity is logged and searchable, empowering governance.**

# Ingest structured and unstructured data.
**Read and write data from structured sources** such as Snowflake, PostgreSQL, SQL Server, Excel, Tableau, and more. **Read and write data from unstructured sources** such as files and APIs in various formats, including text, JSON and XML.
# Clean and reshape. Ensure data quality.
**Address missing values, correct errors, and reshape data** by transforming, combining, aggregating and filtering.
# Blend and process data in‚Äëdatabase and in‚Äëmemory.
**Build locally with sample data files and promote to your production environment** (such as Snowflake) using the same easy to use components.

# Goodbye Unexplainable Workflows.
**Full configuration is visible on every component. Nothing hidden behind icons.**
# Live, interactive data processing.
**Change parameters, see results live.** Now there is no need to rerun the entire workflow when adding a new component, speeding your time to insight.
# Integrated workflow documentation
**Enables you to recall what you have done, and others in the organization to interpret what you have built.** Since it is integrated as part of the workflow, version history is built in!
# Cloud & Desktop.
**You choose. Same Experience!**. Windows, Mac, Linux or in a browser. Users have the freedom and flexibilty to work in the way they want.
# Explore your data without accidental data overwrites.
As you develop your workflow, data is written to temporary location, so you **never overwrite your production data by mistake.** You can also define multiple lifecycle environments, such as development and production, for every data link.
